+### Canonical AI Action Log Schema
+
+Phase 6 project event logs use one canonical JSON object per JSONL line. The
+schema is intentionally readable by humans and AI agents without a dedicated
+timeline UI, while still preserving structured payloads for editor hooks, AI
+work steps, and runtime gameplay events.
+
+```json
+{
+  "schemaVersion": 1,
+  "protocol": "lux.ai.action_log.v1",
+  "id": "018f0f8a1f7d4f8c93e5cdb71f2d6e5a",
+  "timestampUtc": "2026-05-04T00:00:00.0000000Z",
+  "projectPath": "/path/to/unity-project",
+  "source": "unity-editor",
+  "actor": "user",
+  "category": "editor",
+  "type": "selection.changed",
+  "summary": "Selection changed.",
+  "message": "Selection changed.",
+  "severity": "info",
+  "success": true,
+  "metadata": {
+    "correlationId": "corr-1"
+  },
+  "redactionMetadata": {
+    "policyVersion": "lux.redaction.v1",
+    "applied": false,
+    "redactedCount": 0,
+    "redactedFields": [],
+    "redactionClasses": []
+  },
+  "retentionMetadata": {
+    "policyVersion": "lux.retention.v1",
+    "policyName": "project-jsonl-30d-or-10000",
+    "lifecycleState": "active",
+    "retentionDays": 30,
+    "maxEntries": 10000,
+    "expiresAtUtc": "2026-06-03T00:00:00.0000000Z",
+    "cleanupEligible": false,
+    "cleanupReason": ""
+  },
+  "payload": {
+    "kind": "editor-action",
+    "eventType": "selection.changed",
+    "summary": "Selection changed.",
+    "status": "completed",
+    "attributes": {
+      "objectCount": 1
+    }
+  }
+}
+```
+
+Required top-level fields:
+
+| Field | Type | Description |
+| :--- | :--- | :--- |
+| `schemaVersion` | number | Canonical event schema version. Phase 6 writes `1`. |
+| `protocol` | string | Protocol identifier, currently `lux.ai.action_log.v1`. |
+| `id` | string | Stable per-event identifier. Use a GUID/UUID-style value or another producer-stable unique id. |
+| `timestampUtc` | string | UTC ISO-8601 timestamp captured at event creation time. |
+| `projectPath` or `projectId` | string | Project scope. JSONL files are project-scoped; CLI/API read responses must include `projectPath`, and event producers should write one of these when available. |
+| `source` | string | Producer such as `unity-editor`, `unity-runtime`, `codex`, `opencode`, or `lux-gateway`. |
+| `category` | string | Broad class such as `editor`, `ai-action-log`, `runtime`, `scene`, `tool`, `input`, `log`, `screenshot`, or `hierarchy`. |
+| `type` | string | Stable event type used for filtering, for example `selection.changed`, `ai.step.completed`, or `enemy_death`. |
+| `summary` | string | Short redacted human-readable summary for compact AI context. |
+| `message` | string | Redacted user-facing detail. May match `summary` for compact events. |
+| `payload` | object | Structured event-specific payload. Keep values as JSON types, not stringified JSON. |
+| `redactionMetadata` | object | Metadata proving redaction policy application without leaking original sensitive values. |
+| `retentionMetadata` | object | Metadata describing lifecycle and cleanup policy for project JSONL retention. |
+
+Optional top-level fields:
+
+| Field | Type | Description |
+| :--- | :--- | :--- |
+| `actor` | string | Initiator, for example `user`, `agent`, `codex`, `opencode`, or a tool name. |
+| `action` | string | Legacy-compatible action name. Prefer matching `type` for new events. |
+| `target` | string | Redacted target path, object name, scene name, asset id, or runtime entity id. |
+| `severity` | string | `debug`, `info`, `warning`, or `error`; defaults to `info` for Unity-originated records. |
+| `success` | boolean | Whether the step/action completed successfully. |
+| `status` | string | Producer state such as `started`, `completed`, `failed`, or `cancelled`. |
+| `tool` | string | Tool or skill name when the event is emitted by an AI/tooling workflow. |
+| `sessionId` | string | Session identifier for editor, AI, gateway, or runtime producer grouping. |
+| `correlationId` | string | Cross-event correlation id for a command, tool execution, or request. |
+| `metadata` | object | Small redacted scalar metadata for indexing and compatibility. |
+| `projectId` | string | Stable project identifier when `projectPath` is unavailable or intentionally suppressed. |
+
+Payload required fields:
+
+| Field | Type | Description |
+| :--- | :--- | :--- |
+| `kind` | string | One of `editor-action`, `ai-work-step`, `runtime-gameplay-event`, `tool-command`, or `gateway-signal`. |
+| `eventType` | string | Same semantic event type as top-level `type`, kept for payload-local readers. |
+| `summary` | string | Redacted payload-local summary. |
+
+Payload optional fields:
+
+| Field | Type | Description |
+| :--- | :--- | :--- |
+| `status` | string | Payload-local state, normally mirroring top-level `status` when present. |
+| `target` | string | Redacted payload-local target. |
+| `attributes` | object | Event-specific JSON attributes. Values may be strings, numbers, booleans, nulls, arrays, or nested objects after redaction. |
+
+Compatibility notes:
+
+- Older gateway stream envelopes use `schema_version`, `event_id`,
+  `captured_at_utc`, and `session_id`. Readers should continue accepting those
+  aliases and normalize them to `schemaVersion`, `id`, `timestampUtc`, and
+  `sessionId` for AI action log output.
+- Redaction must run before JSONL persistence, HTTP responses, and WebSocket
+  broadcasts. Redaction metadata may name classes such as `credential`,
+  `authorization-header`, `private-key`, `project-path`,
+  `gameplay-sensitive`, or `oversize-text`, but must not include raw values.
+- Retention metadata is required for persisted Phase 6 records so cleanup can
+  enforce both age-based and count-based policies without inspecting payloads.
+
 Supported Phase 1 categories are `playmode`, `scene`, `log`, `tool`, `input`,
 `screenshot`, and `hierarchy`. Some categories are skeleton/demo events in this
 slice; production fidelity is deliberately deferred.
